race.description: Happy 70Th Paul Egan Fillies & Mares Maiden Plate
race.comment: GRAND MILLESIME (6) looks well placed to break through. Three runs to date have all been strong, just finding one better when in the market at Donald over 1350m, beaten a head. No issue going to the slightly longer trip here and she should get a lovely run near the speed. CARDAMOM (4) ran a good race on debut at Kilmore over 1200m when working home late. She should appreciate the rise in trip and looks a threat with natural improvement. GROOVY GRAN (7) is a filly by Toronado on debut for the Hayes yard. She's trialled well enough for this and looks well placed first time out. SOURCE OF DELIGHT (2) ran a solid race in tougher company first up at Pakenham behind a smart winner who has won a good race since. Fitter now and will take some beating.
